67.6	United_States_Secretary_of_Defense	United States Secretary of Defense	The Secretary of Defense is the head and chief executive officer of the Department of Defense, an Executive Department of the Government of the United States of America. This position corresponds to what is generally known as a Defense Minister in many other countries. The Secretary of Defense is appointed by the President with the advice and consent of the Senate, and is by custom a member of the Cabinet and by law a member of the National Security Council.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/USSecDefflag.svg/120px-USSecDefflag.svg.png
